-- Foxconn to Make Solar Panels for SunEdison in Mexico
-- B y   E h r e n   G o o s s e n s
-- 2013-04-23T14:43:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-23/foxconn-to-make-solar-panels-for-sunedison-in-mexico.html
A unit of Foxconn Technology Group,
the Taipei-based maker of products including  Apple Inc. (AAPL) ’s
iPhone, agreed to make solar panels for  MEMC Electronic
Materials Inc. (WFR) ’s SunEdison unit in Mexico.  Foxconn’s Fox Energy will manufacture as much as 350
megawatts of solar panels for MEMC at a Juarez plant, St.
Peters, Missouri-based MEMC said today in a statement.  SunEdison has developed 989 megawatts of solar farms and
has 2.6 gigawatts of projects under development, according to
the statement. MEMC is the biggest U.S. maker of polysilicon
after Hemlock Semiconductor Corp.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ehren Goossens in  New York  at 
 egoossens1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
